cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the synthesis of indoor scenes and images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The proposed method uses a probabilistic grammar model (cs.AI) to represent indoor scenes and encodes contextual relations using Markov Random Fields (cs.LG). The evaluation of the synthesized rooms involves human subjects, which suggests a potential application in natural language processing (cs.CL).
